warm up A>B was a bit heavier than i am used to. 
I used the auto belay and climbed up a 5c route and down a 6a... 
It was actually more like 50 moves, but I felt almost like getting flash pumped so I stopped, took a break and did 4 x 6a boulders (kilter 45 deg.) on the kilter board, again it felt a bit heavy as a warm up, but not too bad. 

I have became too used to my warm up routine and the body needs adjusting to the new regime, maybe?

for the FB 100% i used the lattice edge. 
my max was 25kg, so i decided to try 22.5kg.
I completed the first hang but it felt like my absolute limit, so, I dropped to 20kg, it felt better, but it did not feel like i had 2 seconds spare, i decided to try again with 20kg and see if it next attempt feel better, it was the same, and the last attempt i failed at 6 seconds. 
so it did not go so well... 
maybe the warm up was heavier than I am used to, maybe i did not took enough rest after warm up, maybe I just need to drop the weight even more?

Boulder Project V6-V7 (Kilter 45 deg.)
with the first boulder i made good progress but did not completed then. 
I surprised myself with the second boulder and completed it just before the 20 min limit. 
the third boulder i did not complete but again surprised myself when i sticked a move that felt a bit too hard for me at the beginning. 

I tried to stick to the 2.5 min between attempts but most times I felt i needed more time to recover, so it was more like 3 min between attempts...  
It felt very different than normal kilter sessions, i realised that i normally take shorter breaks and the quality of the attempts is no that good, yesterday was different, I was more focus on recruiting, something i struggle with. 

the time of the whole session was perfect, but I think i need to stretch it a bit and have a longer break between the warm up and the FB100% exercises. maybe?

עדכון לגבי איך הלך העדכון היום:
בתרגיל פינגרבורד בהתחלה עשיתי עם 15 קילו. הסט השלישי כבר היה לי קשה ובקושי סיימתי, הסט הרביעי הצלחתי רק 8 שניות.

במתח בסוף עשיתי עם 7.5 קילו ולדעתי זה היה בול מבחינת מאמץ.

מבחינת התוכנית כולה, אני אצטרך עוד להכיר אותה טוב יותר. לא הגעתי בכלל לחלק של ה4-5ים שאחרי הפרויקטים, פשוט לא נשאר לי זמן.
היו לי בערך שעתיים ורבע לאימון.
אצטרך כנראה לתת יותר זמן (שזה אפשרי עבורי) וגם פשוט להכיר אותה ופחות לבדוק בטלפון מה לעשות.
גם חלק מהמושגים עדיין היו לי חדשים.

Home Workout

- Fingerboard Session
4 Sets of 12 Sec Hangs (start with +12.5 Kg) with 2-3 Min rest between sets
- General Fitness Session

Shrugs - with weights, 4 sets of 8-10 repetitions.

Plank to Push-Up - 3 sets of 10 repetitions for each side.

Pull Ups - 4 Sets of 6 Reps with Weight (so that you have 1 Rep in reserve) with 2-3 Min rest between sets, when too easy add Weight.
Initial weight - 7.5kg

- Stability and Flexibility Training
Side Plank - hold the position for 30-45 seconds on each side.

Finish with Flexibility and Stretching Exercises:
Upper Back Stretch - Stand in a doorway, place both hands on the door frame at shoulder height and step forward until you feel a stretch in the upper back and shoulders. Hold for 30 seconds.
Trapezius Stretch - Sit on the floor, spread your legs apart and lean your body towards one leg, trying to touch the toes. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat on the other side.
Forearm and Hip Stretch - Stand and clasp one hand with the other behind your back, stretching the muscle. Hold each hand for 30 seconds. Then, perform a hip stretch by placing one foot on the opposite knee while folding the body forward.
Hamstring Stretch - Sit on the floor with one leg extended and the other bent inward. Lean your body towards the extended leg. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat with the other leg.
Shoulder Stretch - Standing or sitting, bring one arm across the body and support it with the other hand so that the arm passes in front of the body. Hold this position for 30 seconds and repeat with the other arm.
